column5: Our cottage was fine, my parents place had a huge white pine come crashing down on their roof               oh well, might as well go fishing
Time to fix the date on the camera! LOL.  Wow...the trees that came down there are unreal!  I hope no one was in the cottage or was hurt when the storm blew through!  Nice fish by the way!
WOW, that's lousy luck, sure hope they get everything fixed up fast.
That's crazy!  I too hope things are back to normal soon for everyone up there.  Couple of nice fish though.    Smartass, that's something I would say.  lol!
Wow tough break Chris!  Don't you guys leave for Nakina soon?
I'd say that calls for a massive bonfire! As long as nobody was hurt, it could have been worse I suppose.  S.

yeah, everytime I take the battery out of the camera to charge it, the date needs to be reset   we cancelled, I threw my back out the day before we were supposed to leave, I'm pretty useless now, I'm also disappointed we didn't get to Muskrat
According to Mike Borger, thats no big deal, only a couple of petunias blown the opposite of lean.

Really sorry to hear that Chris. I can relate, I threw my back out two weeks before the Attawapiskat trip, but it healed in time. Did you ever end up working something out with Martin?    It's a heavy wind gust Albert, not a tornado LOL!  A bit touchy don't you think?
